    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Galium labradoricum are its antioxidant and antimicrobial properties, which are mainly attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids in the plant. The anti-inflammatory activity of Galium labradoricum is due to its saponins and triterpenoids, which are known to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. Additionally, the plant exhibits analgesic and antispasmodic properties, which can be attributed to the presence of volatile oils, specifically borneol and camphor, that have a relaxing effect on the muscles and a pain-relieving effect. The antimicrobial activity of Galium labradoricum is particularly useful in treating infections, while its antioxidant properties help in protecting the body from oxidative stress and damage. The analgesic and antispasmodic properties of the plant make it a potential treatment for muscle spasms and pain relief.",
